Commentary Text: Chetan Sakariya to Rahul, out Caught by Rahul Tewatia!! Special catch from Tewatia who takes it right on the edge of the ropes, with the ball behind him, then tosses it up as he goes over the boundary, before running back in, diving forward and grabbing it again. See it so often these days. It was decently struck by Rahul. Was in the slot for him with Sakariya missing the blockhole. Tried clearing the midwicket boundary and would've done so if not for Tewatia. Rahul c Rahul Tewatia b Chetan Sakariya 91(50) [4s-7 6s-5]

Commentary Text: Chris Morris to Pooran, out Caught by Chetan Sakariya!! A golden duck for Pooran who falls to a brilliant catch. This is a nothing ball and Morris is really lucky to get away with it, let alone get a wicket. Slower short ball down leg, Pooran pulls it fine. It's going to the left of Sakariya at short fine leg who flies across, gets both hands and latches onto it. The third umpire is checking whether the ball is touching the ground when he falls down. Commentary Text: Chetan Sakariya to Mayank, out Caught by Samson!! Edged and gone. Sakariya has got his first IPL wicket. That was a fuller length delivery just outside off, Mayank backed away and looked to cream it over covers but ended up edging it to the keeper. Huge wicket indeed. The opening pair mostly does well for the Kings but not tonight. Tried to preempt and ended up edging it. Sakariya is glad. He is joyous. He is on top of the world. From being a net bowler to being a part of this huge league, it has been a wonderful journey. Mayank c Samson b Chetan Sakariya 14(9) [4s-2]

Commentary Text: Arshdeep Singh to Samson, out Caught by Hooda! RR fall a few meters short of the boundary, and a few millimeter short of Samson's sweet spot! A valiant effort from Samson, but in vain, as he picks a pace-off ball and tries to loft it over wide long-off, but ends up handing a regulation (but pressure) catch to Hooda at the boundary. He looks down in disappointment, but chin-up young man! Even the denied single may have been uncalled for, but it was in an effort to win the game. Tough end for Samson. Commentary Text: Shami to Stokes, out Caught&Bowled!! There's a collision between Shami and Rahul as they go for the catch. Shami has held on. Could've been nasty this, but thankfully both are okay as well. Back of a length on off, not short enough to pull. Stokes goes for it nevertheless, the urgency necessitated by the required rate. It goes straight up off the top-edge. And by straight up I mean it would've landed right back on Stokes. He moves away though at the last moment. Both Rahul and Shami have eyes for the ball. Somoehow the catch is taken. Stokes c and b Shami 0(3)
